The paper deals with information extraction from documents using deep neural networks, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) research. Therefore, cs.CL and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of end-to-end data and the lack of word-level labels, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research. Finally, the paper involves parsing and extracting information from documents, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
